The family of Sho Madjozi has already left Limpopo to welcome her from Los Angels in the USA. They left Polokwane around 5am. The Tsonga Rapper Madjozi is returning back to South Africa after she won the BET Award for Best International Act over a week ago. She is expected to arrive in Mzansi around 12:00. Her family, together with Limpopo Provincial Department of Sport, Arts and Culture, will welcome her at OR Tambo International Airport. The Tsonga rapper has made history as the first South African female to win the award. The 27-year-old, was nominated alongside Teniola Apata (Nigeria), Headie One and Octavian from the UK, Jokair and Nesly (France) and our very own AKA. 